node.title: Night at the Ruins
node.description: Night view of the Ruins at Barnsley Gardens, Adairsville, GA.

node.title: Silent Swirls
node.description: I've tried to get this shot several times, but the light just hasnt been right.  When I hiked up the Chinabee Silent Trail a few weeks ago- it finally was.  The only problem was that the pool in front was loaded with trash and debris.  After "working for the shot" I was able to get several pretty good ones.

node.title: Curves
node.description: The curve of this current running through the stream provides a nice path over the sunlit rocky bottom.  Taken along the Chinnabee Silent Trail just outside CheahaState Park.

node.title: Line of sight
node.description: As the day was getting brighter I had to improvise to reduce my light.  For this shot I balanced along the edge of another fall and placed my tripod beneath an overhanging rock.  Still not sure it was worth it, but my wife seemed to like the shot. Thoughts?

node.title: Eye of the falls
node.description: Made my way up yesterday to Cheaha between short rain showers.  Once the rain stopped the light was perfect for photographing waterfalls and I was able to get some shots that just haven't turned out for me before. With such a defined "eye" this swirl reminded me a lot of a hurricane image on radar.

node.title: Still here.
node.description: Thought B&W was more appropriate for this old barn and landscape in Franklin, NC.  Hit "L" to view larger on black!
